<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="type material">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Type material.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
1 male (CAU), China: Fujian Province, Mt. Wuyishan, Sangang, 735 m, 
<geoCoordinate direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="9" value="28.246334">27°74.78'N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="9" value="118.1385">117°68.31'E</geoCoordinate>
, light trap, 12 Jul. 2009, Li Shi and Xiaoyan Liu. Paratypes: 2 males, the same data as holotype, (CAU); 6 males, the same locality, 16 Aug. 2006, Hui Dong, (HIST).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="male">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Male.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Forewing length 15.6-16.0 mm. Distance between ocelli about as wide as diameter of the ocellus. Head slightly wider than pronotum, with an obscure quadrate dark stigma on frons and a brown area covering ocelli (Fig. 1a); compound eyes black and antennae dark; maxillary palpi brown. Pronotum with obscure rugosities and dark brown anterior and lateral margins, thorax mostly brown (Fig. 1a); wing membrane subhyaline, veins brown; legs brown but distal half of femora and basal one fourth and distal one sixth of tibia dark brown, tarsi dark brown (Fig. 2d).</paragraph>
